kind: llman.sdd.delta
ops[5]{op,req_id,title,statement,from,to,name}:
  modify_requirement,la1,"core-layer","System MUST provide a base domain/ layer hosting domain vocabulary types including AgentMessage and ModelKind and XyChunk and ALL pure data types consumed by two or more layers (such as SessionEntry variants, SourceInfo, SkillInfo, PromptTemplate, CompactionSettings, AgentLifecycleEvent). System MUST provide a separate runtime_protocol/ layer hosting the trait contracts (XyModel, XyTool, SessionStore, EventSink, SandboxEngine, BashExecutor, SecretResolver, ResourceLoader, TrustStore, ExportIo) so that no layer must import crate::infra merely to reference a shared data type or to declare a port.",null,null,null
  modify_requirement,la2,"downward-dependency","infra/ modules MUST NOT import any crate::agent symbol; agent/ modules MUST NOT import any concrete infra/ type (only via runtime_protocol); interactive/ modules MUST NOT import crate::agent or crate::infra except in the in-process composition root. domain/ MUST have zero crate:: internal dependencies and runtime_protocol/ MUST only depend on domain/.",null,null,null
  modify_requirement,la7,"runtime-residence","All runtimes (provider, tool, session storage, exec-env, bash executor, secret resolution, resource loader, export I/O) MUST live under infra/; agent/ MUST hold them only as Arc<dyn Port> injected at the composition root from runtime_protocol/; agent/ MUST NOT call any infra constructor or borrow infra exec primitives directly.",null,null,null
  modify_requirement,la9,"arch-guard-expanded","The architecture guard MUST enforce via a guard test (src/tests.rs::arch_guard) all of: no infra file imports crate::agent, no agent file imports ANY concrete crate::infra type via a full scan of crate::infra:: in production code, and no interactive file imports crate::agent or crate::infra except the in-process driver composition root; the scan scope MUST reconcile with la2 (agent imports no concrete infra type).",null,null,null
  add_requirement,la14,"no-core-rename-shim","System MUST NOT retain a pub use domain as core backward-compatibility shim; all call sites MUST be updated to crate::domain in one pass.",null,null,null
op_scenarios[5]{req_id,id,given,when,then}:
  la1,"shared-types-in-domain",a pure data type is needed by both agent/ and infra/,the type is declared and imported,"both layers import it from crate::domain and runtime_protocol from crate::runtime_protocol"
  la2,"agent-no-infra-concrete","an agent/ source file is compiled","it references crate::infra::provider::OpenAIProvider or crate::infra::tools::BashTool","the build or guard rejects it"
  la7,"executor-not-in-agent",the bash executor is located,its source file is inspected,it lives under infra/ and agent/ reaches it only via an injected port
  la9,"guard-catches-tools-leak","a new agent/ file adds use crate::infra::tools::BashTool in production code",the architecture guard runs,the guard fails and reports the offending file path
  la14,"no-shim",the source tree is grepped for backward shims,the grep runs,"zero matches for pub use domain as core or similar re-exports"
